    <div class="ms-col-content">
      <h2></h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="ms-row">
    <div class="ms-col-content">
      <p>Digital change in higher education takes universities on a journey that may be adventurous and challenging. Organizing educational technologies is an ongoing process that touches on major pillars of the university’s organization: Digital teaching is in interplay with university leadership, strategy, infrastructures and resources, incentive structures and network. Considering each of these areas is vitally important to tap the full potential of educational technology and ensure its longevity. This guide offers some roads to get there.</p>
<p>The practitioner's field guide is a companion on the journey of digital teaching and translates findings from our research on digital change in universities into recommendations for practice. The recommendations are addressed to university leaders as well as faculty leaders, teachers and staff. The guide includes six thematic areas and equips readers with discussion impulses, examples and concrete steps. Background info on the underlying research, on the contributors and on how to use the guide can be accessed through the menu above.</p>

      
      <h3>Keywords</h3>
      <p>Responsible business, ethical standards, platforms, business model, good governance, digital economy</p>
      



      

      

