<section>
  <div class="container">
     <div class="ms-row ms-row-two ms-text" id="partial_4">
  <div class="ms-col-content">
    <h2 id='heading-4' >Summary</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="ms-col-marginal">
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="ms-row ms-row-two ms-text" id="partial_5">
  <div class="ms-col-content">
    <p>Digital platforms have left their mark on European economies and societies. Globally dominant platforms, like Google, Amazon, Facebook, Apple, and Microsoft (GAFAM), have come to be seen as a menace to fair competition, sovereignty, data protection and even democracy. Platform capitalism is facing a deep spiritual crisis, which could well be the precursor to an economic one as well.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="ms-col-marginal">
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="ms-row ms-row-two ms-text" id="partial_6">
  <div class="ms-col-content">
    <p>The <em>Strategic Guide to Responsible Platform Business</em> highlights alternative strategies that platform organisations can pursue if they seek to acknowledge and mitigate platform capitalism’s problematic tendencies. It is based on the premise that the dominant platform business model that GAFAM have established may indeed lead to harmful outcomes for European societies, and yet, these outcomes are not inherent to all platform business models. The Guide acknowledges tensions and trade-offs in platform managers’ decision-making, but it also showcases ways to balance corporate, user, and societal interests in a more sustainable fashion. </p>
  </div>
  <div class="ms-col-marginal">
    
  </div>
</div>

<div class="ms-row ms-row-two ms-plugin ms-plugin-video" id="partial_7">
  <div class="ms-col-content">
    
<div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9" id="video-youtube-QiSr-AZHJnw">
  <div class="youtube" data-id="QiSr-AZHJnw">
  </div>
</div>

  </div>
  <div class="ms-col-marginal">
    
<aside class="ms-aside-caption">
  <p><strong>Responsible Platform Business:</strong>
    
    <br>Nicolas Friederici and Vili Lehdonvirta in conversation on corporate governance guidelines, self-regulation of European digital platforms, and the challenges faced when defining guiding principles<br>
    
  </p>
</aside>







